    <body>
        <div id="header">knitting class</div>
        
        <p>WEEK 1</p>
        <p>you'll learn...</p>
        <p><ol>
                <li>casting on</li>
                <li>knitting</li>
                <li>purling</li>
                <li>stocking/stockinette stitch</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <p>you'll need...</p>
        <p><ol>
                <li>one ball of yarn (50 grams or more); DK, aran, worsted, or chunky weight recommended</li>
                <li>one set of straight knitting needles; size 3.5mm - 5mm recommended (or size recommended on yarn ball band)</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <p>WEEK 2</p>
        <p>you'll learn...</p>
        <p><ol>
                <li>binding off/casting off</li>
                <li>weaving in ends</li>
                <li>more basic stitches - rib, garter, seed</li>
                <li>kfb (increase stitch)</li>
                <li>yo (increase stitch)</li>
                <li>k2tog/p2tog (decrease stitch)</li>
                <li>slipping knitwise & purlwise</li>
                <li>selvedge edge</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <p>you'll need...</p>
        <p><ol>
                <li>one ball of yarn (50 grams or more); DK, aran, worsted, or chunky weight recommended</li>
                <li>one set of straight knitting needles; size 3.5mm - 5mm recommended (or size recommended on yarn ball band)</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <p>WEEK 3</p>
        <p>you'll learn...</p>
        <p><ol>
                <li>knitting in the round</li>
                <li>magic loop</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <p>you'll need...</p>
        <p><ol>
                <li>one ball of yarn (50 grams or more); DK, aran, worsted, or chunky weight recommended</li>
                <li>one circular knitting needle; size 3.5mm - 5mm recommended (or size recommended on yarn ball band)</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <p>WEEK 4</p>
        <p>you'll choose one of these topics:</p>
        <p><ol>
                <li>intro to cabling</li>
                <li>intro to lace</li>
                <li>intro to colorwork</li>
                <li>intro to socks</li>
            </ol>
        </p>

